The decrease in cost of revenues in Insurance of $6.7 million was primarily due to decreases in employee-related costs of $4.0 million, lower travel costs of $4.4 million and foreign exchange gain, net of hedging of $2.2 million. This was partially offset by higher infrastructure and technology costs of $3.3 million, primarily related to the work from home enablement and other operating costs of $0.6 million. Gross margin in Insurance increased by 110 bps during the year ended December 31, 2020 compared to the year ended December 31, 2019, primarily due to expansion in margin in certain existing clients, partially offset by COVID-19 related incremental expenses during the year ended December 31, 2020.
