Revenues for the year ended December 31, 2019 were $991.3 million, up $108.2 million, or 12.3%, compared to the year ended December 31, 2018.
Revenue growth in Insurance of $35.2 million was primarily driven by expansion of business from our existing clients and new wins aggregating to $38.6 million. This was partially offset by $3.4 million mainly attributable to the depreciation of the Australian dollar, Indian rupee, U.K. pound sterling and South African ZAR against the U.S. dollar during the year ended December 31, 2019 compared to the year ended December 31, 2018. Insurance revenues were 34.9% and 35.2% of our total revenues in 2019 and 2018, respectively.
